This paper deals with the problem of predicting types of entities and relations in a knowledge base, which is a common task in natural language processing and machine learning. The paper proposes a new approach for making predictions about unseen entities or entity pairs, which involves learning an aggregation function of the vectors of observed columns for that row. This approach is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
